{"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Testing with Forge","modules":[{"name":"Forge"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Forge provides three mechanisms for overriding dependencies in tests, listed in order","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of preference. All examples use Swift Testing (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Suite"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#expect"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Scoped-Overrides-with-withOverrides-Preferred","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Scoped Overrides with withOverrides (Preferred)"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Container\/withOverrides(_:run:)-3qdpl","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" registers overrides for the duration of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure, then automatically restores the previous state. No manual cleanup required:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test(\"Login succeeds with valid credentials\")","func testLoginSuccess() async throws {","    let mock = MockAuthService(shouldSucceed: true)","","    try await AuthContainer.shared.withOverrides {","        $0.override(\\.authService) { mock }","    } run: {","        let viewModel = LoginViewModel()","        await viewModel.login(username: \"user\", password: \"pass\")","        #expect(mock.loginCalled)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cleanup is guaranteed via "},{"code":"defer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — even if the body throws, overrides are restored."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Both sync and async variants are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Container\/withOverrides(_:run:)-3qdpl","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — synchronous","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Container\/withOverrides(_:run:)-4eui2","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — async (use when your test body contains ","type":"text"},{"code":"await","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Fresh-State-Between-Tests","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Fresh State Between Tests"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SharedContainer\/shared","type":"reference"},{"text":" is a stable ","type":"text"},{"code":"let","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the lifetime of the process — you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"don’t (and can’t) swap the instance. For test suites where every test needs a clean","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"slate, reset the shared container in place with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/resetAll()","type":"reference"},{"text":" in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"suite’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"init","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"code":"resetAll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" clears all cached singletons, cached values, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"registered overrides:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Suite(\"LoginViewModel behavior\", .serialized)","struct LoginViewModelTests {","","    init() {","        AuthContainer.shared.resetAll()","    }","","    @Test(\"Login calls the auth service\")","    func testLoginCallsService() async throws {","        let mock = MockAuthService()","","        try await AuthContainer.shared.withOverrides {","            $0.override(\\.authService) { mock }","        } run: {","            let vm = LoginViewModel()","            await vm.login(username: \"test\", password: \"pass\")","            #expect(mock.loginCalled)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each test gets a fresh starting point with no leftover state from previous tests.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Mark such suites ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".serialized"},{"text":" so the in-place resets don’t race across tests.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Direct-Overrides-Escape-Hatch","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Direct Overrides (Escape Hatch)"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withOverrides"},{"type":"text","text":" closures are impractical, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/override(_:with:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["init() {","    AuthContainer.shared.resetAll()","    AuthContainer.shared.override(\\.authService) { MockAuthService() }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the escape hatch — prefer "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withOverrides"},{"type":"text","text":" wherever possible because direct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overrides require manual cleanup via "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/removeOverride(for:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/resetAll()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"The-TestContainer-Pattern-with-unimplemented","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"The TestContainer Pattern with unimplemented"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/unimplemented(_:file:line:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" makes dependency contracts explicit — any dependency"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that isn’t overridden crashes immediately instead of silently running the wrong code."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is valuable in tests (shown here) and in cross-module proxies (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ModularArchitecture","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use it to define a test container where every dependency fails loudly if called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without being explicitly overridden:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["final class TestAuthContainer: AuthContainer {","    override var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","        provide { unimplemented(\"authService\") }","    }","","    override var networkClient: any NetworkClientProtocol {","        provide { unimplemented(\"networkClient\") }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then in your tests, build the test container as an instance, override only what you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"need, and resolve through it explicitly with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ContainerInject","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test(\"Login success flow\")","func testLoginSuccess() async throws {","    let container = TestAuthContainer()","","    try await container.withOverrides {","        $0.override(\\.authService) {","            MockAuthService(shouldSucceed: true)","        }","        \/\/ networkClient is unimplemented — if login accidentally","        \/\/ calls it, the test fails loudly instead of silently","        \/\/ executing live code","    } run: {","        let authService = ContainerInject(container, \\.authService).wrappedValue","        let vm = LoginViewModel(authService: authService)","        await vm.login(username: \"user\", password: \"pass\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This makes test contracts explicit — you declare exactly which dependencies a test"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exercises. Anything else is a bug."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want the zero-argument ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Inject(\\.x)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to resolve from a test container","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without threading it through initializers, declare that container’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"static var","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SharedContainer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" requirement is only ","type":"text"},{"code":"{ get }","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so a ","type":"text"},{"code":"var","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"satisfies it) and assign it in a ","type":"text"},{"code":".serialized","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" suite’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"init","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Forge permits this;","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it just isn’t the default — prefer the stable ","type":"text"},{"code":"let","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" plus ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container\/resetAll()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"anchor":"Best-Practices","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Best Practices"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefer "},{"code":"withOverrides","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — automatic cleanup prevents test state leakage"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"resetAll()"},{"type":"text","text":" in suite "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — gives each test a fresh starting point"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unimplemented"},{"type":"text","text":" for test containers"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — makes dependency boundaries explicit"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"code":".serialized","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on suites"}]},{"type":"text","text":" that reset or mutate "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shared"},{"type":"text","text":" — prevents data races"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use protocol return types","type":"text"}]},{"text":" on container properties — this is what makes mocks","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"substitutable for live implementations","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/OverrideBuilder","doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/unimplemented(_:file:line:)"],"title":"Testing and Contracts","anchor":"Testing-and-Contracts","generated":true}],"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/TestingWithForge"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/forge\/testingwithforge"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Mock dependencies in tests using scoped overrides, container reset, and explicit te